==English==

===Etymology===
From {{affix|en|never|alt1=Never|land}}. Compare [[Utopia]], which is semantically Ancient Greek {{affix|grc|οὐ|gloss1=not, no|τόπος|gloss2=place, region|nocat=1}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An ideal or imaginary place; a [[dreamworld]].

====Usage notes====
* This term was most famously used in {{w|J.M. Barrie}}'s Book, '''{{w|Peter Pan}}''', as the name of the fictional island that the Darling children travel to with the title character.

